<p>The HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade Orchestration service leverages OpenStack Heat to provide
      template-based orchestration for describing a cloud application. It executes OpenStack API
      calls to generate running cloud applications.</p>
<section id="working-with-the-orchestration-service"> <title>Working with the Orchestration Service</title>
<p>To perform tasks using the Orchestration service, you can use the dashboard, API or CLI.</p>
</section>
<section id="UI"> <title>Using the dashboards<!--Removed anchor point UI--><!-- id="UI" --></title>
<p>You can use the <xref
          href="../OperationsGuide/Dashboard/CGH-2-User-Dashboard-how-works.dita#topic6108c2udhw">HP
          Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade Dashboard</xref> to work with the Compute service.</p>
</section>
<section id="API"> <title>Using the API<!--Removed anchor point API--><!-- id="API" --></title>
<p>You can use a low-level, raw REST API access to the Orchestration service. See the <xref href="http://developer.openstack.org/api-ref-orchestration-v1.html" scope="external" format="html" >OpenStack Orchestration API v1 Reference</xref>.</p>
</section>
<section id="cli"> <title>Using the CLI<!--Removed anchor point cli--><!-- id="cli" --></title>
<p>You can use any of several command-line interface software to access the Orchestration service. See the <xref href="http://docs.openstack.org/cli-reference/content/heatclient_commands.html" scope="external" format="html" >OpenStack Command Line Interface Reference</xref>.</p>
  <p>For more information on installing the command-line interface for interacting with services, see <xref href="http://docs.openstack.org/user-guide/content/install_clients.html" scope="external" format="html" >installing the OpenStack command-line clients</xref>.</p>
</section>
